  25:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   @verbatim
  26:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   ==============================================================================
  27:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****                ##### RTC and Backup Domain Operating Condition #####
  28:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   ==============================================================================
  29:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The real-time clock (RTC) and the RTC backup registers can be powered
ARM GAS  C:\Users\bku598\AppData\Local\Temp\cccc1Cy3.s 			page 2


  30:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****        from the VBAT voltage when the main VDD supply is powered off.
  31:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****        To retain the content of the RTC backup registers and supply the RTC when
  32:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****        VDD is turned off, VBAT pin can be connected to an optional standby
  33:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****        voltage supplied by a battery or by another source.
  34:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  35:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] To allow the RTC operating even when the main digital supply (VDD) is turned
  36:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****        off, the VBAT pin powers the following blocks:
  37:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) The RTC
  38:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) The LSE oscillator
  39:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) PC13 to PC15 I/Os, plus PA0 and PC12 I/Os (when available)
  40:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  41:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] When the backup domain is supplied by VDD (analog switch connected to VDD),
  42:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****        the following pins are available:
  43:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) PC14 and PC15 can be used as either GPIO or LSE pins
  44:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) PC13 can be used as a GPIO or as the RTC_AF1 pin
  45:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) PA0 can be used as a GPIO or as the RTC_AF2 pin
  46:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) PC12 can be used as a GPIO or as the RTC_AF3 pin
  47:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  48:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] When the backup domain is supplied by VBAT (analog switch connected to VBAT
  49:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****        because VDD is not present), the following pins are available:
  50:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) PC14 and PC15 can be used as LSE pins only
  51:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) PC13 can be used as the RTC_AF1 pin
  52:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) PA0 can be used as the RTC_AF2 pin
  53:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) PC12 can be used as the RTC_AF3 pin
  54:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  55:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****                    ##### Backup Domain Reset #####
  56:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   ==================================================================
  57:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The backup domain reset sets all RTC registers and the RCC_BDCR register
  58:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****        to their reset values.
  59:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] A backup domain reset is generated when one of the following events occurs:
  60:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) Software reset, triggered by setting the BDRST bit in the
  61:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****         RCC Backup domain control register (RCC_BDCR).
  62:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) VDD or VBAT power on, if both supplies have previously been powered off.
  63:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (#) Tamper detection event resets all data backup registers.
  64:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  65:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****                    ##### Backup Domain Access #####
  66:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   ==================================================================
  67:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] After reset, the backup domain (RTC registers and RTC backup data registers)
  68:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****        is protected against possible unwanted write accesses.
  69:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] To enable access to the RTC Domain and RTC registers, proceed as follows:
  70:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Enable the Power Controller (PWR) APB1 interface clock using the
  71:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****         __HAL_RCC_PWR_CLK_ENABLE() macro.
  72:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Enable access to RTC domain using the HAL_PWR_EnableBkUpAccess() function.
  73:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Select the RTC clock source using the __HAL_RCC_RTC_CONFIG() macro.
  74:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Enable RTC Clock using the __HAL_RCC_RTC_ENABLE() macro.
  75:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  76:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   ==============================================================================
  77:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****                         ##### How to use this driver #####
  78:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   ==============================================================================
  79:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
  80:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Enable the RTC domain access (see description in the section above).
  81:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Configure the RTC Prescaler (Asynchronous and Synchronous) and RTC hour
  82:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****         format using the HAL_RTC_Init() function.
  83:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  84:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   *** Time and Date configuration ***
  85:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   ===================================
  86:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
ARM GAS  C:\Users\bku598\AppData\Local\Temp\cccc1Cy3.s 			page 3


  87:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) To configure the RTC Calendar (Time and Date) use the HAL_RTC_SetTime()
  88:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****         and HAL_RTC_SetDate() functions.
  89:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) To read the RTC Calendar, use the HAL_RTC_GetTime() and HAL_RTC_GetDate()
  90:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****         functions.
  91:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) To manage the RTC summer or winter time change, use the following
  92:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****         functions:
  93:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****         (++) HAL_RTC_DST_Add1Hour() or HAL_RTC_DST_Sub1Hour to add or subtract
  94:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****              1 hour from the calendar time.
  95:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****         (++) HAL_RTC_DST_SetStoreOperation() or HAL_RTC_DST_ClearStoreOperation
  96:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****              to memorize whether the time change has been performed or not.
  97:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c **** 
  98:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   *** Alarm configuration ***
  99:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   ===========================
 100:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 101:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) To configure the RTC Alarm use the HAL_RTC_SetAlarm() function.
 102:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****         You can also configure the RTC Alarm with interrupt mode using the
 103:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****         HAL_RTC_SetAlarm_IT() function.
 104:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) To read the RTC Alarm, use the HAL_RTC_GetAlarm() function.
 105:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 106:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****                   ##### RTC and low power modes #####
 107:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   ==================================================================
 108:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The MCU can be woken up from a low power mode by an RTC alternate
 109:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****        function.
 110:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The RTC alternate functions are the RTC alarms (Alarm A and Alarm B),
 111:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****        RTC wakeup, RTC tamper event detection and RTC timestamp event detection.
 112:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****        These RTC alternate functions can wake up the system from the Stop and
 113:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****        Standby low power modes.
 114:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The system can also wake up from low power modes without depending
 115:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****        on an external interrupt (Auto-wakeup mode), by using the RTC alarm
 116:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****        or the RTC wakeup events.
 117:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..] The RTC provides a programmable time base for waking up from the
 118:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****        Stop or Standby mode at regular intervals.
 119:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****        Wakeup from STOP and STANDBY modes is possible only when the RTC clock
 120:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****        source is LSE or LSI.
 121:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 122:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   *** Callback registration ***
 123:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   =============================================
 124:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 125:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   When the compilation define USE_HAL_RTC_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 126:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   not defined, the callback registration feature is not available and all
 127:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions.
 128:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   This is the recommended configuration in order to optimize memory/code
 129:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   consumption footprint/performances.
 130:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 131:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   The compilation define  USE_HAL_RTC_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
 132:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
 133:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   Use Function HAL_RTC_RegisterCallback() to register an interrupt callback.
 134:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 135:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   Function HAL_RTC_RegisterCallback() allows to register following callbacks:
 136:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) AlarmAEventCallback          : RTC Alarm A Event callback.
 137:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) AlarmBEventCallback          : RTC Alarm B Event callback.
 138:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) TimeStampEventCallback       : RTC Timestamp Event callback.
 139:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) WakeUpTimerEventCallback     : RTC WakeUpTimer Event callback.
 140:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Tamper1EventCallback         : RTC Tamper 1 Event callback. (*)
 141:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Tamper2EventCallback         : RTC Tamper 2 Event callback.
 142:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Tamper3EventCallback         : RTC Tamper 3 Event callback. (*)
 143:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback              : RTC MspInit callback.
ARM GAS  C:\Users\bku598\AppData\Local\Temp\cccc1Cy3.s 			page 4


 144:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback            : RTC MspDeInit callback.
 145:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 146:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   (*) value not applicable to all devices.
 147:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 148:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 149:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   and a pointer to the user callback function.
 150:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 151:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   Use function HAL_RTC_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
 152:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   weak function.
 153:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   HAL_RTC_UnRegisterCallback() takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
 154:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   and the Callback ID.
 155:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   This function allows to reset following callbacks:
 156:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) AlarmAEventCallback          : RTC Alarm A Event callback.
 157:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) AlarmBEventCallback          : RTC Alarm B Event callback.
 158:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) TimeStampEventCallback       : RTC Timestamp Event callback.
 159:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) WakeUpTimerEventCallback     : RTC WakeUpTimer Event callback.
 160:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Tamper1EventCallback         : RTC Tamper 1 Event callback. (*)
 161:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Tamper2EventCallback         : RTC Tamper 2 Event callback.
 162:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) Tamper3EventCallback         : RTC Tamper 3 Event callback. (*)
 163:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback              : RTC MspInit callback.
 164:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback            : RTC MspDeInit callback.
 165:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 166:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   (*) value not applicable to all devices.
 167:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 168:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   By default, after the HAL_RTC_Init() and when the state is HAL_RTC_STATE_RESET,
 169:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions:
 170:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   examples AlarmAEventCallback(), TimeStampEventCallback().
 171:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   Exception done for MspInit() and MspDeInit() callbacks that are reset to the
 172:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   legacy weak function in the HAL_RTC_Init()/HAL_RTC_DeInit() only when these
 173:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 174:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   If not, MspInit() or MspDeInit() are not null, HAL_RTC_Init()/HAL_RTC_DeInit()
 175:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   keep and use the user MspInit()/MspDeInit() callbacks (registered beforehand).
 176:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   [..]
 177:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_RTC_STATE_READY state only.
 178:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   Exception done for MspInit() and MspDeInit() that can be registered/unregistered
 179:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   in HAL_RTC_STATE_READY or HAL_RTC_STATE_RESET state.
