 216:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   * @brief    Initialization and Configuration functions
 217:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   *
 218:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c **** @verbatim
 219:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****  ===============================================================================
 220:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****               ##### Initialization and de-initialization functions #####
 221:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****  ===============================================================================
 222:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****    [..] This section provides functions allowing to initialize and configure the
 223:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****          RTC Prescaler (Synchronous and Asynchronous), RTC Hour format, disable
 224:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****          RTC registers Write protection, enter and exit the RTC initialization mode,
 225:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****          RTC registers synchronization check and reference clock detection enable.
 226:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****          (#) The RTC Prescaler is programmed to generate the RTC 1Hz time base.
 227:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****              It is split into 2 programmable prescalers to minimize power consumption.
 228:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****              (++) A 7-bit asynchronous prescaler and a 15-bit synchronous prescaler.
 229:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****              (++) When both prescalers are used, it is recommended to configure the
 230:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****                  asynchronous prescaler to a high value to minimize power consumption.
 231:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****          (#) All RTC registers are Write protected. Writing to the RTC registers
 232:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****              is enabled by writing a key into the Write Protection register, RTC_WPR.
 233:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****          (#) To configure the RTC Calendar, user application should enter
 234:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****              initialization mode. In this mode, the calendar counter is stopped
 235:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****              and its value can be updated. When the initialization sequence is
 236:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****              complete, the calendar restarts counting after 4 RTCCLK cycles.
 237:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****          (#) To read the calendar through the shadow registers after Calendar
 238:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****              initialization, calendar update or after wakeup from low power modes
 239:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****              the software must first clear the RSF flag. The software must then
 240:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****              wait until it is set again before reading the calendar, which means
 241:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****              that the calendar registers have been correctly copied into the
 242:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****              RTC_TR and RTC_DR shadow registers. The HAL_RTC_WaitForSynchro() function
 243:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****              implements the above software sequence (RSF clear and RSF check).
 244:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c **** 
 245:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c **** @endverbatim
 246:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   * @{
 247:Drivers/STM32WBxx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32wbxx_hal_rtc.c ****   */
